HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 15
By Atchley
A RESOLUTION to recognize Dollywood on the occasion of the
park's fortieth anniversary.
WHEREAS, Dolly Parton opened Dollywood in her native Sevier County on May 3,
1986; in the ensuing decades, the park has become one of the world's leading family
destinations, ranked No. 1 among U.S. theme parks by TripAdvisor; and
WHEREAS, in honor of its fortieth anniversary, Dollywood has many special events and
surprises planned for the 2025 season, with the season passholder preview day set for March
14, 2025, and a new fortieth anniversary show debuting Memorial Day weekend; and
WHEREAS, additionally, a new drone and fireworks show honoring the fortieth
anniversary season will take place as part of Dollywood's Smoky Mountain Summer
Celebration, and a new opening ceremony will occur at the beginning of each operating day
during the 2025 season; and
WHEREAS, the Imagination Playhouse, which features plays based on books from
Dolly's Imagination Library, becomes a permanent fixture during the 2025 season, offering its
much-loved shows for younger guests from March through the end of September, and the
theater will offer a rotation of playhouse favorites guests have enjoyed through the years; and
WHEREAS, also in celebration of the fortieth anniversary, Heartsong: The Movie will be
remastered and relocated to Dreamsong Theater as part of The Dolly Parton Experience; the
film will run in conjunction with Heidi Parton's Kin & Friends; and
WHEREAS, through much growth and many changes over the years, Dollywood has
remained true to its mission: to create a welcoming environment where families can enjoy
making memories together; and
